### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword123"
}

### 2. Login to get Access Token
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=john@example.com&password=securepassword123

> {% client.global.set("auth_token", response.body.access_token); %}

### 3. Upload a Report
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/reports/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file_type"

pdf
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="medical_report.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./medical_report.pdf
--WebAppBoundary--

> {% client.global.set("report_id", response.body.id); %}

### 4. Ask AI to Analyze Report (ALSO extracts and saves metrics to DB automatically)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/ai/analyze-report
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "report_id": "{{report_id}}"
}

### 5. Ask a RAG Question
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/ai/query-report
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "report_id": "{{report_id}}",
  "question": "What specifically did the doctor mention?"
}


# ==========================================
# PHASE 3: ANALYTICS & INSIGHTS 
# ==========================================

### 6. Get Frontend Time-Series Metrics Trends
# Use this to power your React/Vue Line Charts!
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/metrics/trends
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}


### 7. Get Raw Extracted Database Metrics for a Report
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/metrics/{{report_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}


### 8. Run Comparative Engine
# Compares the provided report against the user's historical past averages automatically
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/reports/compare/{{report_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}


### 9. Generate AI Historical Health Insights
# Holistic timeline text analysis!
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/ai/health-insights
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}


# ==========================================
# PHASE 4: ACTION AGENTS
# ==========================================

### 10. Add Emergency Contact
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/emergency/add-contact
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "phone_number": "+1234567890",
  "relation": "Spouse"
}

### 11. Trigger Panic Button / Manual Alert
# Simulates the LLM finding a HIGH risk report and firing the SMS/Email Engine!
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/emergency/trigger-alert
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 12. Schedule a Medication Reminder
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/medications/add
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "medicine_name": "Lisinopril",
  "dosage": "10mg",
  "time": "08:00",
  "start_date": "2026-03-27T00:00:00Z"
}

### 13. List Active Medications
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/medications/list
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 14. Delete a Scheduled Medication
# Replace {med_id} with ID from GET /medications/list
DELETE http://localhost:8000/api/v1/medications/REPLACE_WITH_UUID
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

# ==========================================
# PHASE 5: MULTI-AGENT ORCHESTRATION 
# ==========================================

### 15. Orchestrator Engine: Autonomous Process Report
# Executes the Analyzer -> Diagnosis -> Insights pipeline instantly!
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/ai/process-report
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "report_id": "{{report_id}}"
}

### 16. Orchestrator Engine: User RAG Query
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/ai/agent-query
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "report_id": "{{report_id}}",
  "question": "Did the secondary diagnostic agent flag any lipid issues?"
}
